This paper deals with hypergraph decomposition methods used for answering queries and solving constraint satisfaction problems, which are common topics in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of checking certain properties of these decomposition methods, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of these methods in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
